data.meta_description: Waymarking.com is a way to mark unique locations on the planet and give them a voice. While GPS technology allows us to pinpoint any location on the planet, mark the location, and share it with others, Waymarking is the toolset for categorizing and adding unique information for that location.

Felton Covered Bridge Park - Felton, California

Posted by: hotshoe

N 37° 03.120 W 122° 04.275

10S E 582581 N 4101044

Small county park featuring the historic covered bridge

Waymark Code: WM4W7E

Location: California, United States

Published By: silverquill

Views: 13

Parking entrance is off Graham Hill Road near the junction of Highway 9. There is a lovely modern playground, a few picnic tables, volleyball, and of course, the bridge.
